Name: time
Description: Time utilities and scheduler for tool actions.
Version: 1.0

Overview:
This toolset provides current time, and lets you schedule tool calls at a
specific time or on a repeating interval.

Commands:
- time_now
  Get current time.
  Parameters:
  - tz (string, optional): UTC or offset like +05:30.
  - format (string, optional): strftime format.
  - epoch (boolean, optional): Return Unix epoch seconds.

- time_parse
  Parse an ISO datetime into components.
  Parameters:
  - iso (string, required)

- time_format
  Format an ISO datetime with strftime.
  Parameters:
  - iso (string, required)
  - format (string, required)

- time_add
  Add seconds to a time.
  Parameters:
  - iso (string, required)
  - seconds (number, required)

- time_diff
  Difference in seconds between two times (end - start).
  Parameters:
  - start (string, required)
  - end (string, required)

- time_convert_tz
  Convert a time to another timezone.
  Parameters:
  - iso (string, required)
  - tz (string, required)

- time_sleep
  Sleep for N seconds (blocking).
  Parameters:
  - seconds (number, required)

- time_schedule_once
  Schedule a one-time tool call.
  Parameters:
  - tool_name (string, required): Tool to call.
  - tool_params (object, optional): Tool params dict.
  - run_at (string, optional): ISO datetime.
  - delay_seconds (number, optional): Delay in seconds.
  - tz (string, optional): Timezone for run_at.

- time_schedule_interval
  Schedule repeating tool calls.
  Parameters:
  - tool_name (string, required)
  - tool_params (object, optional)
  - interval_seconds (number, required)
  - start_at (string, optional): ISO start time.
  - tz (string, optional)
  - repeat_count (integer, optional): How many times.
  - end_at (string, optional): ISO end time.
  - immediate (boolean, optional): Run immediately before first interval.

- time_schedule_cron
  Schedule tool calls using a cron expression.
  Parameters:
  - tool_name (string, required)
  - tool_params (object, optional)
  - cron (string, required): 5-field cron.
  - tz (string, optional)

- time_cancel
  Cancel a scheduled job.
  Parameters:
  - job_id (string, required)

- time_schedule_cancel
  Cancel a scheduled job (alias of time_cancel).
  Parameters:
  - job_id (string, required)

- time_list_jobs
  List scheduled jobs.

Usage Examples:
- time_now
- time_now tz="UTC" format="%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"
- time_schedule_once tool_name="gmail_send" tool_params={"to":["a@b.com"],"subject":"Hi","body":"Hello"} delay_seconds=60
- time_schedule_interval tool_name="capture_screen" tool_params={} interval_seconds=300 repeat_count=3
- time_schedule_cron tool_name="gmail_send" tool_params={"to":["a@b.com"],"subject":"Hi","body":"Hello"} cron="0 9 * * *" tz="UTC"
- time_cancel job_id="<id>"

Behavior Notes:
- Scheduled jobs run in background threads.
- Job results and errors are stored in-memory while the process runs.
- Jobs are persisted to toolsf/time/tool/time_jobs.json and restored on startup.

Dependencies:
- Python standard library (datetime, threading)
- croniter (optional) for cron scheduling

Dependencies:
- Python standard library (datetime, threading)
